{{distinguish|UAE T20x}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox cricket tournament main | name = Abu Dhabi T20 Trophy | image = Abu Dhabi T20 Logo.jpg | imagesize= | caption = | country = United Arab Emirates | administrator = Abu Dhabi Cricket | cricket format = 20-over cricket | first = [[2018 Abu Dhabi T20 Trophy|2018]] | next = | last = | tournament format = | participants = 6 | champions= [[Lahore Qalandars]] (1st title) | most successful = [[Lahore Qalandars]] (1 title) | qualification = | most runs = {{flagicon|PAK}} [[Sohail Akhtar]] (193) | most wickets = {{flagicon|PAK}} Raja Farzan (6) | website= [http://www.abudhabit20.ae abudhabit20.ae] | current = }}
The '''Abu Dhabi T20 Trophy'''<ref name="ADT20">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/23964288/abu-dhabi-host-teams-six-countries-t20-tournament |title=Abu Dhabi to host teams from six countries in T20 tournament |accessdate=4 July 2018 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> is a 20-over [[cricket]] franchise tournament held in the [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref name="CI">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/23693053/emirates-cricket-board-new-tournament-threatens-ties-pcb |title=Emirates Cricket Board's new tournament threatens ties with PCB |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> The [[2018 Abu Dhabi T20 Trophy|first edition]] of the tournament was played in October 2018.<ref name="ADT20"/><ref name="AB">{{cite web |url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/sport/398147-new-international-t20-cricket-league-coming-to-uae |title=UAE set to host new international T20 cricket league |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=Arabian Business}}</ref> Six franchise teams took part in the first edition.<ref name="TN">{{cite web |url=https://www.thenational.ae/sport/cricket/emirates-cricket-board-announce-plans-for-uae-twenty20-league-1.736516 |title=Emirates Cricket Board announce plans for UAE Twenty20 league |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=The National}}</ref> The [[International Cricket Council]] (ICC) sanctioned the competition in June 2018.<ref name="EC">{{cite web |url=http://emiratescricket.com/whatsnew/UAE's%20first%20T20%20Franchise%20Cricket%20League%20to%20be%20formally%20unveiled%20later%20this%20month |title=UAE'S First T20 Franchise Cricket League to be Formally Unveiled Later This Month |accessdate=4 June 2018 |work=Emirates Cricket}}</ref>
[[Lahore Qalandars]] won the first edition after beating [[Titans (cricket team)|Titans]] by fifteen runs in the final.<ref name="Winner">{{cite web |url=https://www.thenational.ae/sport/cricket/abu-dhabi-t20-lahore-qalandars-win-title-with-titans-victory-1.777858 |title=Abu Dhabi T20: Lahore Qalandars win title with Titans victory |accessdate=6 October 2018 |work = The National}}</ref>
==Teams== The first edition of the tournament featured the following teams:<ref name="ADT20"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfnews.com/sport/uae/cricket/auckland-aces-confirmed-for-abu-dhabi-t20-1.2281656 |title=Auckland Aces confirmed for Abu Dhabi T20 |work=Gulf News |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>
* [[Boost Defenders]] of the [[Shpageeza Cricket League]] * [[Hobart Hurricanes]] of the [[Big Bash League]] * [[Lahore Qalandars]] of the [[Pakistan Super League]] * [[Titans (cricket team)|Titans]] of the [[Ram Slam T20 Challenge]] * [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire Vikings]] of the [[Twenty20 Cup|T20 Blast]] * [[Auckland cricket team| Auckland Aces]] of the [[Super Smash (cricket)|Super Smash]]
