{{Unreferenced|date=March 2007}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Regional de Los Andes | nickname = Estadio trasandino | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = File:Estadio trasandino.jpg | caption = Estadio Regional de Los Andes | fullname = | former_names = | owner = | location = [[Los Andes, Chile|Los Andes]], [[Chile]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = {{Start date|1996|03|29}}<ref name="suenos"/> | renovated = | reopened = | surface = grass | architect = | capacity = 3.300 persons<ref name="suenos">{{cite web |url=http://www.cdtrasandino.com/estadio.php |title=Nuestro Teatro de los Sueños |work=Trasandino de Los Andes |deadurl=yes |archive-url=https://archive.is/20070702184959/http://www.cdtrasandino.com/estadio.php |archivedate=2 July 2007 |accessdate=23 September 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = }} '''Estadio Regional de Los Andes''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Los Andes, Chile|Los Andes]], [[Chile]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Club Deportivo Trasandino de Los Andes|Trasandino]]. The stadium holds 3,313 people and was built in 1996.
