{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = ''Stadion Utama Riau'' | image = Riau Main Stadium.JPG | location = [[Pekanbaru]], [[Riau]] | coordinates = {{Coord|0|32|59|N|101|26|45.55|E|type:landmark|display=inline, title|name=Riau Main Stadium}} | broke_ground = October 2009 | opened = 2012 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Government of [[Riau]] | operator = Government of [[Riau]] | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[PSPS Pekanbaru]] | seating_capacity = 43,923<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/venues/indonesia/stadion-utama-riau/</ref> }} '''Riau Main Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Pekanbaru]], [[Riau]], [[Indonesia]]. Completed in 2012, it will be used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and hosted the opening and closing ceremonies for the [[2012 Pekan Olahraga Nasional]]. The stadium has a capacity of 43,923.<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/venues/indonesia/stadion-utama-riau/</ref> In July 2012, this stadium hosted AFC U-22 Asian Cup qualification rounds.<ref>[http://www.pekanbaruriau.com/2009/04/info-stadion-utama-pon-riau-2012.html Info Stadion Utama PON Riau 2012<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111207210247/http://www.pekanbaruriau.com/2009/04/info-stadion-utama-pon-riau-2012.html |date=2011-12-07 }}</ref>
