'''W. Hall''' (full name and dates of birth and death unknown) was an English [[cricket]]er who played for [[Hampshire county cricket teams]] organised by the [[Hambledon Club]].

Hall made one known [[first-class cricket|first-class]] appearance, playing for Hampshire against [[Kent county cricket teams|Kent]] at [[Sevenoaks Vine]] in 1782.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/62.html ''CricketArchive'' – Kent v Hampshire 1782].  Retrieved on 18 January 2011.</ref>  The match also marked the known first-class debuts of both [[David Harris (English cricketer)|David Harris]] and [[Joey Ring]].<ref>Haygarth, pp.51–52.</ref>

