{{Infobox stadium | name = Winkin Sports Complex | nickname = winkin sesh winkin complex | image = | fullname = | location = [[Bangor, Maine|Bangor]], [[Maine]] | coordinates = {{coord|44.8247|-68.7944 |format=dms |region:US-ME_type:landmark |display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2001 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Husson University]] | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = | capacity = 3,000 | record_attendance = | dimensions = | scoreboard = }}
'''Winkin Sports Complex''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Bangor, Maine]]. It is home of the [[Husson University]] baseball, field hockey, and football teams.<ref>{{cite web | title = Winkin Sports Complex | publisher = Husson University Athletic Department | url = http://www.husson.edu/?cat_id=334 | accessdate = 2008-02-17 }}</ref> The ballpark has a capacity of 3,000 people and opened in 2004.<ref>{{cite web | title = The Wink | url = http://mysite.verizon.net/charliesballparks/stadiums/husson.htm | accessdate = 2008-02-17 }}</ref> It was formerly the home of [[Bangor Lumberjacks]].
The complex was named in honor of retired head baseball coach [[John Winkin]].
